Job Description:
 Study design briefs and determine requirements
 Conceptualize original website design ideas that bring simplicity and user friendliness to complex barriers.
 Schedule projects and define budget constraints
 Conceptualize visuals based on requirements
 Prepare rough drafts and present ideas to peers and executive level stakeholders.
 Establish and promote design guidelines, best practices and standards.
 Produce graphical content and creation of powerful visuals from textual content.
 Design content and layout for print, website, digital panels, and other stated projects
 Develop illustrations, logos and other designs using software or by hand
 Implement, execute, and maintain approved design tools and style guides.
 Use appropriate colours and layouts for each graphic
 Test graphics across various media
 Amend designs after feedback
 Ensure final graphics and layouts are visually appealing and on-brand
 Other ad-hoc duties as assigned

Requirements:
 Proven graphic designing experience
 A strong portfolio of illustrations or other graphics
 Experience in F&amp;B industry will be advantageous
 Familiarity with design software and technologies like adobe illustrator, photoshop and Dreamweaver will be an advantage
 Excellent visual design skills with sensitivity to user-system interaction.
 Ability to solve problems creatively and effectively.
 Up to date with the latest Web trends, techniques, and technologies.
 Dedicated to deadlines and having excellent time-management to work on several projects simultaneously, efficiently, and independently
 Strong presentation and communication skills, verbal and written
 Ability to work methodically under tight timeline
 Able to start work within short notice